    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nIn diff mode, E315 is issued by\n\n1. :diffput (or dp in normal mode)\n2. multiple lines\n3. to a nonexisting or an empty file\n\n`E315: ml_get: Invalid lnum: <#diffed lines + 1>`.\n\nThis does not happen when any of the conditions are fulfilled.\n\n`:set diffopt-=linematch:40`, for compliance with vim, does not resolve the issue. \n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```sh\nrm -f foo\n# or\ntrue > foo\n```\n\n```\nnvim -d --clean <(seq 2) foo\n:diffput \" E315: ml_get: Invalid lnum: 3\n:qa!\n\nnvim -d --clean <(seq 1) foo\n:diffput \" no error\n:qa!\n\nnvim -d --clean foo <(seq 2)\n:diffget \" no error\n:qa!\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nE315 is not issued.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.12.0-dev-19a3b67\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno, vim 9.1.2114\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nEndeavourOS\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nghostty 1.2.3-arch2\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-ghostty\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from repo",
