            "body": "There is another problem that 'cursorline' is not drawn:\n```shell\nnvim --clean -d <(seq 2) foo -c 'windo set cursorline nofoldenable | wincmd t'\n```\nWith `dp` after startup, the cursorline is not drawn in the other window.\n\nThis one also happens in Vim.\n\nAlso, in Nvim the 'cursorline' in the other window returns after `:redraw!`, unless `laststatus=0` is set, in which case redrawing doesn't do thing. In Vim `:redraw!` also doesn't do anything with `laststatus=0`, but with `laststatus=1` or `laststatus=2` the ruler on the other window disappears on `:redraw!`.",
